\section*{PRECONCEPTION CARE}

\section*{Introduction}

Preconception care is the provision of biomedical, behavioral and social health interventions to women and couples before conception occurs (WHO, 2012). It aims at improving their health status and reducing behaviors and individual and environmental factors that contribute to poor maternal and child health outcomes. Its ultimate aim is to improve maternal and child health, in both the short and long term.

\section*{Life course - when to intervene?}

