\section*{PLACENTA PREVIA}
- Placenta Previa refers to the implantation of the placenta over or near the internal os of the cervix. ${ }^{7}$
- All placentas overlying the os (to any degree) are termed as Previa and those near to but not overlying the os are termed low-lying ${ }^{15}$.
- Placenta Previa is commonly diagnosed by ultrasonography in the third trimester, often between 28 and 32 weeks ${ }^{16}$.

Epidemiology: The estimated global prevalence of placenta previa was 5.2 per 1000 pregnancies in 2014'

