Vaginal examination - Sterile speculum examination and digital vaginal examination at intervals of 4 hrs

The following criteria should be present to call it normal labour
- Spontaneous onset
- Spontaneous expulsion of a single mature foetus
- Presenting by vertex
- Through the birth canal within a reasonable time (not less than 3 hours
