\section*{Prostaglandins}

They induce ripening of the cervix and uterine contractions.

\section*{In living foetus:}
- Dinoprostone intracervical gel ( 3 g gel $/ 0.5 \mathrm{mg}$ dinoprostone) or Prostaglandin $\mathrm{E}_{2} 3 \mathrm{mg}$ tablet is placed in the cervix but not beyond the cervical internal os. The application can be repeated after 6-8hours, not to exceed 3 doses in 24 hours.
- Dinoprostone vaginal pessary 10 mg is placed in the posterior fornix of the vagina for 24 hour

\section*{In dead foetus:}
- Extra-amniotic and intra-amniotic prostaglandin F2a.

\section*{Misoprostol ${ }^{\mathbf{5}}$}

Misoprostol, a prostaglandin El analog with a mechanism of action that stimulates uterine contractility and cervical ripening. This is a heat stable tablet at room temperature and cheap making it accessible in LMIC.
- Oral misoprostol ( $200 \mu \mathrm{~g}$, 2-hourly) is recommended for induction of labour ${ }^{6}$
- Vaginal low-dose misoprostol ( $25 \mu \mathrm{~g}$, 6-hourly) is recommended for induction of labour.
- Misoprostol is not recommended for women with previous caesarean section. ${ }^{7}$

