\section*{VBAC Scoring System}

This is a model used to predict the likelihood of a successful vaginal delivery following a prior cesarean section. This prediction is done when patients are admitted for delivery or labor. The VBAC scoring system is also described as a tool used to identify patients at low, medium and high risk for vaginal delivery after caesarean section (VBAC).

Several scoring systems and tools have been used to predict a successful TOLAC.The commonest scoring system is that of Flamm and Geiger. ${ }^{19}$ The Flamm model has been associated with reasonable predictability for VBAC as well as consistent identification of women at risk for failed trial of labour. The Flamm score has been shown to have a sensitivity of $72 \%$ and specificity of $76 \%$ for prediction of successful VBAC.

