Septic shock is a life-threatening clinical syndrome caused by decreased tissue perfusion and oxygen delivery, as a result of severe infection and sepsis. ${ }^{9,15}$

\section*{Common causes of septic shock}
- Septic abortion
- Chorioamnionitis
- Postpartum endometritis
- Pyelonephritis
- Pelvic abscess
- Puerperal sepsis
- Respiratory tract infections etc.

