- Site (in relation to the bladder neck and ureteral orifices), size and degree of scarring determine the complexity of obstetric fistula. In arriving at this conclusion, the following are ascertained: number of fistulous tracts, degree of scarring of the vagina and urethral sphincter.
- Other considerations include length of residual urethra (which determines the degree of urethral reconstruction to be performed and the patient's future continence), residual bladder capacity, and status of the ureters
