![](https://cdn.mathpix.com/cropped/2025_11_24_1f5d3abc0b734f89226ag-471.jpg?height=596&width=852&top_left_y=539&top_left_x=1004)

\section*{Step Two}
- Perform cervical antiseptic prep
- Use antiseptic soaked sponge to clean cervical os
- Start at os then spiral outward without retracing areas
- Repeat until os has been completely covered by antiseptic
![](https://cdn.mathpix.com/cropped/2025_11_24_1f5d3abc0b734f89226ag-471.jpg?height=515&width=655&top_left_y=1127&top_left_x=1142)

\section*{Step Three}
- Perform a para cervical block with 20 cc of $1 \%$ lidocaine or 10 cc of $2 \%$ lidocaine
- Inject small amount of lidocaine (I-2cc) in to the cervix at the tenaculum site ( 12 o'clock)
- Inject the remaining lidocaine in equal amounts at the cervical vaginal junction at 2,4,8 and 10 o'clock
- Always aspirate before injecting to prevent intravascular injection of lidocaine
![](https://cdn.mathpix.com/cropped/2025_11_24_1f5d3abc0b734f89226ag-471.jpg?height=501&width=844&top_left_y=1627&top_left_x=1013)

\section*{Step Four: Dilate Cervix}
- Observe no-touch technique when dilating the cervix and during aspiration.
- Instruments that enter the uterine cavity should not touch your gloved hands, the patient's skin, the woman's vaginal walls, or unsterile parts of the instrument tray before entering the cervix
- Use mechanical dilators or progressively larger cannulae to gently dilate the cervix to the right size.

\section*{Step Five: Insert Cannula}
- While applying traction to the tenaculum, insert cannula through the cervix, just past the os and into the uterine cavity
- Do not insert the cannula forcefully
![](https://cdn.mathpix.com/cropped/2025_11_24_1f5d3abc0b734f89226ag-472.jpg?height=507&width=817&top_left_y=205&top_left_x=1022)

Step Six: Prepare the Aspirator
- Position the plunger all the way inside the cylinder
- Have collar stop in place with tabs in the cylinder hole
- Push valve buttons down and forward until they lock (I)
- Pull plunger back until arms snap outward and catch on cylinder base (2)
![](https://cdn.mathpix.com/cropped/2025_11_24_1f5d3abc0b734f89226ag-472.jpg?height=550&width=831&top_left_y=750&top_left_x=1019)

\section*{Step Seven: Suction Uterine Contents}
- Attach the prepared aspirator to the cannula
- Release the vacuum by pressing both buttons
- Evacuate the contents of the uterus by gently and slowly rotating the cannula $180^{\circ}$ in each direction, using an in-and-out motion
- When the procedure is finished, depress the buttons and disconnect the cannula from the aspirator
- Alternatively, withdraw the cannula and aspirator without depressing the buttons
![](https://cdn.mathpix.com/cropped/2025_11_24_1f5d3abc0b734f89226ag-472.jpg?height=561&width=821&top_left_y=1310&top_left_x=1027)

