\section*{Prevention of Postpartum Hemorrhage}

\section*{Correction of anemia in the antenatal period}

The WHO recommends daily iron and folic acid supplementation with 30 mg to 60 mg of elemental iron and $400 \mu \mathrm{~g}(0.4 \mathrm{mg})$ of folic acid. This should be started as soon as pregnancy is confirmed or at preconception if previous problems with folic acid deficiency have been encountered.

\section*{Active Management of the Third Stage of Labor}

Available evidence supports routine use of active management of the third stage of labor (AMTSL) by all skilled birth attendants, regardless of where they practice; AMTSL reduces the incidence of PPH, the quantity of blood loss, and the need for blood transfusion, and thus should be included in any program of intervention aimed at reducing death from PPH ${ }^{1.20}$

The components of AMTSL include:
- Administration of oxytocin or another uterotonic drug within I minute after birth of the baby after ruling out multiple gestation
- Controlled cord traction
- Uterine massage after delivery of the placenta

