\section*{Mechanism of UBT Free Flow System}

The free flow system is an open system that:
- Stops bleeding as soon as pressure on uterus wall is slightly higher than systolic BP
- Allows for the physiological process of contraction and retraction of myometrium
- Allows water to fill the balloon in less than one minute
- Adjusting the height of the bag controls pressure exerted on uterus wall
- Allows water to be expelled from the balloon back to the supply bag reducing the size of the balloon: Free Flow Mechanism (FFM)
- Allows pressure control that will prevent tissue necrosis if used together with brace/ compression sutures

