\section*{MATERNAL \& PERINATAL DEATH SURVEILLANCE AND RESPONSE}

\section*{Introduction}

Maternal and Perinatal Deaths Surveillance and Response (MPDSR) constitutes a quality improvement approach to identify how many maternal deaths occur (Surveillance), what the underlying causes of death and associated factors are (Review), and how to implement actions to reduce the number of preventable stillbirths and maternal and neonatal deaths (Response)

Reviewing mothers and perinatal deaths contributes towards saving their lives from lessons learnt ${ }^{1}$ Further introduction of the maternal early obstetric warning signs; birth preparedness and complication readiness ${ }^{2}$; and skilled birth attendance ${ }^{3}$ can alleviate the calamity associated with death ${ }^{4}$. In 99\% of the world's maternal deaths, still births and neonatal deaths occur in LMIC and in over $80 \%$ these are preventable ${ }^{5,6}$. Currently in Kenya the maternal mortality ratio, perinatal mortality rate and the neonatal mortality rate are at 362/100,000 live births; 29/1000 live births and 22/1000 live births respectively ${ }^{7}$.

Kenya made maternal death notification mandatory in 2004 and the facility-based Maternal Death Review (MDR) was relaunched in 2009.The National Committee for Maternal and Perinatal Death Surveillance and Response (MPDSR) and National MPDSR Secretariat was established within the MOH in 2014. The National guidelines for Maternal and Perinatal Death Surveillance and Response (MPDSR) were launched in 2016 and the first Confidential Enquiry into Maternal Deaths (CEMD) was published 2017.

There is urgent need to build national capacities for MPDSR and address the employment of tools that capture the maternal- neonate dyad and the underlying factors that culminated in death.

\section*{Rationale for MPDSR guidelines}

Need to align guidelines with revised WHO MDSR technical guidance by strengthening the response component. The guidelines should have
- A structured multi-sectoral response
- Adopt Zero-reporting principle
- The guidelines should incorporatae the new devolved structure of governance
- Align with SDGs

\section*{Purpose of MPDSR}

Is to take actions to eliminate preventable maternal and perinatal deaths
Efforts to eliminate preventable maternal and perinatal deaths include:
- Scaling up training of Emergency Obstetrics and New-born Care (EmONC) and MPDSR countrywide
- Eliminating user fees for maternity services through the Free Maternity Services Initiative (Linda Mama program) since 2013

\section*{Early pregnancy identification:}

Identification of early pregnancies is critical to full documentation of maternal mortality especially those related to abortion and ectopic pregnancies
- Linkage with Civil Registration \& Vital Statistics
- Link with the assistant chiefs who register deaths at the community level (verbal autopsy)
- ICD -II training needed and should include sensitization of community based MPDSR personnel.
- Instituting maternal and perinatal death surveillance and response mechanisms

Employing review of also near misses as a proxy indicator to evaluate the underlying drawbacks in the quality of care from medical, obstetric and perinatal pathophysiology and the health system in which services are provided.

