\section*{Processes for reporting of MPDSR}
- All Maternal deaths (MDs) are notified within 24 hrs
- All Perinatal Deaths (PDs) are notified within 72 hours
- All Maternal and Perinatal Death Notification forms should be uploaded into the KHIS after notification
- All facilities to send data on number of Maternal Deaths together with the weekly IDSR data. This includes Zero Reports of no maternal death occurred in the week
- All Maternal deaths at community level are reviewed by community MPDSR committees within 30 days of death
- All Maternal deaths (MDs) \& Perinatal deaths (PDs) at facility level are reviewed by Facility MPDSR Committee within 7 days of death
- All completed MDR and Verbal Autopsy forms to be uploaded into KHIS after the Review
- All facilities should continue sending the monthly reports (MOH 711) which includes the total number of maternal deaths and number of maternal deaths reviewed
- All data is being aggregated and analysed at Sub county, County and National levels by MPDSR committees.
- Facility MPDSR committees shall meet monthly or more frequently if more MDs occur to discuss the MDs and PDs and near miss cases to improve quality of care

