- If none of the above found any catheter with multiple holes can be placed

Fluids: Peritoneal dialysis fluids used can be:
Commercially prepared PD fluids which come in strengths of $1.5 \%$, $2.5 \%$ and $4.25 \%$
If not available, you can use Hartman's Solution and 50\% dextrose (addingI5 ml of 50\% dextrose 500 ml of Hartman's solution gives $1.5 \%$ solution)

Process: the process of acute peritoneal dialysis involves inflow of the peritoneal dialysis fluid into the peritoneal cavity, dwelling in the cavity to allow exchange and then outflow into a drainage bag.

\section*{Prescription:}
- Fill volume: volume to be infused: start with $15 \mathrm{ml} / \mathrm{kg}$
- Inflow: usually about 10 minutes
- Dwell time: start with 30 minutes
- Outflow: time allowed to flow out: about 20 minutes
- It is important to monitor renal function daily during dialysis. Once the indication for dialysis is achieved dialysis should be stopped. It is important to seek expert advise during the process of dialysis.

Follow up: Arrange long term follow up for all babies

\section*{RESPIRATORY DISTRESS}

\section*{Definition}

Tachypnoea>60 breaths/min, grunting, chest retraction with or without cyanosis

\section*{Causes}

\section*{I. Pulmonary}
- Respiratory distress syndrome (RDS) (surfactant deficiency) especially in preterm babies
- Pneumonia
- Aspiration syndromes (meconium, feeds)
- Pulmonary haemorrhage,

\section*{2. Airway}
- Laryngomalacia
- Choanal atresia
- Micrognathia

\section*{3. CNS}
- Seizures,
- Birth asphyxia,
- Intracranial haemorrhage

\section*{4. Metabolic}
- Hypoglycemia,
- Electrolyte derangements Temperature instability
- Congenital heart diseases especially those with cardiac failure

\section*{Management}

Take history \& do thorough examination to identify the cause of distress Assess the severity of the distress using the Silverman-Anderson score

\section*{Investigations}

\section*{For all babies}
- Chest X-ray
- Full blood count including a manual PBF CRP
- Blood gas analysis, Blood sugar
- Specific investigation according to suspected cause

\section*{Specific Treatment}
- Treat the underlying cause
- Start antibiotics
- Start IV fluids

