\section*{Signs of anaemia}

Unexplained apnoea,
1. Tachycardia (rate $>160 / \mathrm{min}$ for $>48 \mathrm{hrs}$ ),
2. Poor weight gain ( $<10 \mathrm{~g} / \mathrm{kg} /$ day ) with adequate feed intake and environmental temperature for 7 days,
3. Signs of CCF.

\section*{Top up' transfusions for any neonate}

Use ABO \& Rh D compatible with mother and baby. (If mother or baby is Rh negative always use Rh negative blood)

Use packed cells as much as possible
