- For mild cases give syrup Amoxicillin 62.5 mg tid $\times 5 / 7$ or Cloxacillin 62.5 mg tid $\times 5 / 7$
- For extensive skin lesion admit and start treatment with Crystalline Penicillin and Gentamicin or intravenous Flucloxacillin

Dosage:
IM or IV Crystalline Penicillin 50,000U/kg 12 hourly
- Counsel the mother on subsequent care:
- Return baby for review after 2days
- Return immediately if baby becomes sicker. (See features of neonatal septicaemia)

