\section*{Investigation}

HSV PCR testing of CSF for suspected HSV encephalitis.

\section*{Treatment}
I.V Acyclovir $20 \mathrm{mgs} / \mathrm{kg} /$ dose 8 hrly -14days for local infection and 21 days for disseminated infection.

\section*{Cytomegalovirus}

Features of intrauterine growth restriction. May be asymptomatic in the neonatal period but may present with jaundice, hepatosplenomegaly, petechiae Investigation
- Urine PCR for CMV
- Specific IgM

\section*{Prevention}
- Adequate treatment of maternal infection during pregnancy, labour and delivery
- Vaginal swabbing with antiseptic during labour (e.g. hibitane)
- Clean delivery Clean/sterile equipment
- Observe infection control at all levels of handling baby
- Handwashing before and after handling baby
- Early initiation of breast feeding
- Exclusive breast feeding
- Avoid overcrowding especially in the newborn unit

\section*{NEONATAL TETANUS}

\section*{Definition}

Any neonate with normal ability to suck and cry during the first 2 days of life and who, between 3 and 28 days of age, cannot suck normally and becomes stiff or has spasms (i.e. jerking of the muscles)

\section*{Diagnosis}
- Inability to feed orally
- Muscle spasms
- Clenched mouth - risus sardonicus
- Stiff body that is arched backward like a bow (opisthotonus)
- Stiff arms and legs

\section*{Prevention}
- Ensure that all pregnant mothers are given Tetanus Toxoid according to the National Immunization schedule
- Provide education on the importance of the 5cleans (see section on appropriate cord care)
- Appropriate cord care

\section*{Management}

Sedate the baby by giving IV or rectal:
- Phenobarbitone $20 \mathrm{mg} / \mathrm{kg}$ stat; or
- Diazepam $0.2 \mathrm{mg} / \mathrm{kg}$ over 3 minutes. Repeat every 30 minutes upto 3 doses
- Do not exceed $2 \mathrm{mg} / \mathrm{kg} / 24 \mathrm{hrs}$

\section*{Maintain sedation with:}
- Phenobarbitone $5 \mathrm{mg} / \mathrm{kg} /$ dayin2doses
- Chlorpromazine $2 \mathrm{mg} / \mathrm{kg} /$ day
(These can also be given as continuous infusion).

\section*{While baby is sedated:}
- Give antibiotics - IV Crystalline Penicillin 50,000units/kg 12 hourly
- Anti Tetanus immunoglobulin should be administered where available for established cases
- Clean the cord thoroughly
- Pass a nasogastric tube for feeding

\section*{Subsequent Care:}
- Counsel the mother
- Keep baby in a quiet room
- Frequent monitoring of vital signs-watch respiration
- Avoid too much handling
- Keep umbilical cord clean and dry
- Paint cord with providine iodine
- Feed Expressed Breast Milk through nasogastric tube (See section on feeding)
- Refer to ICU if facility is available
- Immunize the mother and ask her to complete immunization as per the National schedule
- If baby recovers refer to MCH for immunization

